---
---
<section id="about" class="section about-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-intro">
        <span class="badge badge-maroon">Core Mission</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">A modern, open training ground for developers and designers</h2>
        <p class="about-desc">
          uplb.tools is a collaborative project registry. We aim to address common student struggles—like mapping out room schedules or managing academic pathways—by building robust, local-first web applications.
        </p>
        <p class="about-desc">
          Beyond software delivery, our primary goal is mentoring. Students of all skill levels work together, learning industry-standard technologies, version control, and interface design guidelines in a real-world sandbox.
        </p>
        
        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value">2+</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Active projects</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value">100%</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Open source codebases</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value">Local</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Privacy first storage</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="about-values">
        <div class="card value-card">
          <div class="value-header">
            <span class="value-bullet bullet-maroon"></span>
            <h3>Practical Utilities</h3>
          </div>
          <p>We target actual UPLB campus needs. If a tool makes room search or grade simulation faster for the student body, we code and deploy it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card value-card">
          <div class="value-header">
            <span class="value-bullet bullet-green"></span>
            <h3>Mentoring Sandboxes</h3>
          </div>
          <p>We welcome student designers, copywriters, and developers. Every contributor learns through pull-request reviews, feedback loops, and deployment flows.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card value-card">
          <div class="value-header">
            <span class="value-bullet bullet-maroon"></span>
            <h3>No Data Monetization</h3>
          </div>
          <p>We do not run trackers, inject ads, or collect student information. All computations run in the user's browser or as local extensions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about-section {
    background-color: #090b11;
  }
  
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  
  .section-title {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .about-desc {
    font-size: 0.975rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-body);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }
  
  .stat-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  
  .stat-value {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--text-title);
  }
  
  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-body);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
  
  .about-values {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  
  .value-card {
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
  }
  
  .value-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .value-bullet {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  
  .bullet-maroon {
    background-color: var(--brand-maroon-light);
  }
  
  .bullet-green {
    background-color: var(--brand-green-light);
  }
  
  .value-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  
  .value-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-body);
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 968px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 3.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
